@RaulACarrillo @GrkStav Small rate increases can slow inflation without causing mass layoffs.
If rates aren’t allowed to creep up a bit over time, then they won’t be able to be dropped when the economy sours.
Changes should be ideally like a clutch in a manual-transmission car: easy in, quick out.

@RaulACarrillo @GrkStav Wage boosts can quickly be nullified by inflation, so doing nothing could be worse for the net financial situation of workers/families.

